==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Persimmon
<hw>Per*sim"mon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Virginia
Indian.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An American tree (<spn>Diospyros
Virginiana</spn>) and its fruit, found from New York southward. The
fruit is like a plum in appearance, but is very harsh and astringent
until it has been exposed to frost, when it becomes palatable and
nutritious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Japanese persimmon</b></col>, <cd><spn>Diospyros
Kaki</spn> and its red or yellow edible fruit, which outwardly resembles
a tomato, but contains a few large seeds.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persis</ent>⟦br⟧
